          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Respected Principal,\nSchool is good but need to teach some manners to reception, as well as right information to provide. As I went to enquire for next year nursary admission but she said my daughter(Aug 20) is not eligible for next year nursary and as per school age criteria mentioned on website, she is eligible next year nursery as she is not eligible for this year nursery. when I went there she was scrolling insta but showing of like she is so busy than anyone else in this world. I don't like her attitude. School should have policy that staff should talk with parents respectfully. Reception is face of School but due to people like this reputed schools also getting bad reviews. Even after bad writing review I am giving 4 star because good School should not affect because of this type of peoples.\nThanks",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "DAV Public School - Aundh"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Shilpa P"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-07-02",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I recently had the opportunity to observe a school where it was ensured that all students of 7 th std have a fair chance to appear for Sanskrit exams to get that subject as 3 rd language . The school's commitment to inclusivity and providing equal opportunities for every student is truly impressive.\nI would like appreciate  Principal Ma'am and coordinator Deepa ma'am for the  decision to offer every student a fair chance to showcase their abilities and knowledge during the exams has not only boosted their confidence but also instilled a sense of fairness and justice in their young minds.\nWe need such teachers in the schools who does everything just for their students and DAV has such teachers. I am really happy with the school",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
